    {
        "content": "<p>The classical proof I had in mind looked like<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">‚à£</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>‚àí</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">‚à£</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">‚à£</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>‚àí</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>‚àí</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">‚à£</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>œµ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\left|\\frac{2n}{5n +1} - \\frac{2}{5}\\right| = \\left|\\frac{10n - 10n -2 }{5(5n +1)}\\right| = \\frac{2}{5(5n +1)} &lt; \\frac{1}{5n} &lt; \\epsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2533em;vertical-align:-0.4033em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.85em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.85em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.2em;\"></span><span style=\"width:0.333em;height:1.200em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.333em\" height=\"1.200em\" viewBox=\"0 0 333 1200\"><path d=\"M145 15 v585 v0 v585 c2.667,10,9.667,15,21,15\nc10,0,16.667,-5,20,-15 v-585 v0 v-585 c-2.667,-10,-9.667,-15,-21,-15\nc-10,0,-16.667,5,-20,15z M188 15 H145 v585 v0 v585 h43z\"/></svg></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-